features.name: IMS,IMS_C,IMS_HHH Poorly processive, error-prone DNA polymerase involved in untargeted mutagenesis. Copies undamaged DNA at stalled replication forks, which arise in vivo from mismatched or misaligned primer ends. These misaligned primers can be extended by PolIV. Exhibits no 3'-5' exonuclease (proofreading) activity. May be involved in translesional synthesis, in conjunction with the beta clamp from PolIII
Sigma70_r4,Sigma70_r4_2 COG1191 DNA-directed RNA polymerase specialized sigma subunit

RecU Endonuclease that resolves Holliday junction intermediates in genetic recombination. Cleaves mobile four-strand junctions by introducing symmetrical nicks in paired strands. Promotes annealing of linear ssDNA with homologous dsDNA. Required for DNA repair, homologous recombination and chromosome segregation
Phage_Mu_F Phage Mu protein F like protein
Peptidase_S78_2 Putative phage serine protease XkdF
Phage_TAC_12 Phage tail assembly chaperone protein, TAC
